       =======================================
 
 			 :: 	   Veejay, a visual instrument for GNU            ::
	                                 http://veejay.dyne.org 



 Veejay - a 'visual' instrument and realtime video sampler

Veejay is a visual instrument and real-time video sampler.
It allows you to "play" the video like you would play a piano.
While playing, you can record the resulting video directly to disk (video sampling).

Trigger samples, apply realtime fx (120+), scratch, mix and record , never stopping the video. Excellent for live video performing.
Main Features

# Client/Server architecture
# Soft Realtime
# Native YUV processing
# Frame accurate
# Loop based editing (always playing)
# Non destructive editing
# Trickplay (scratch, marker, speed, direction)
# Mix your videos the FX chain
# 120 built-in effects incl. luma , chroma key, invert,solarize,etc
# Effect parameter animation
# Support for FreeFrame and Frei0r
# Support for truetype fonts
# Audio playback through Jack
# Load Quicktime, AVI and rawdv movie files
# Video output to SDL, OpenGL
# Full support for DV and MJPEG
# Live clip loading
# Live harddisk recording
# Live sample sequencing
# Live text
# Live camera(s) support
# Can stream over the network
# Deck save/restore
# Crash Recovery
# Support for Open Sound Control
# Support for pure-data through sendVIMS external
# Free Software (GNU GPL)




Install
=======

See file 'INSTALL'

See doc/Howto_Compile.html
See doc/Howto_Compile_on_Ubuntu.html

Documentation
=============

See the directory 'doc' in this package, it contains usefull documentation.


Running
=======

Start 1 or more Veejay servers:
$ veejay my-movie-A.avi
$ veejay -p 4490 my-movie-B.avi
 
Start a graphical user interface:

$ gveejayreloaded ( -n )
$ gveejay


Start using the launcher

$ vlaunch



